Credit: Michael Philbin & Jacob Lenerts

Make a function to sort a list by deleting the elements out of order.
Order being least to greatest or greatest to least depending on a boolean parameter.

Example 1:

Input:  {1,6,3,5,6,5,5,6,7,4,9} LtG
Output: {1,3,5,6,7,9}

Example 2:

Input:  {9,4,7,6,5,5,6,5,3,6,1} GtL
Output: {9,7,6,5,3,1}
